						<summary>

						<p>Slab lyning infront of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land to Bhattuḍu son of Hanumantha, a artisan (who prepared an image) by Sāḷuva Gōvindarāju for his own merit. In characters of 16th century A.D.</p>						

